06:46.956 --> 06:48.039
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

06:48.063 --> 06:50.063
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

06:56.263 --> 06:57.363
- [sighs]
- Having trouble

06:57.415 --> 06:59.999
with your closing?

07:00.051 --> 07:02.769
No, it's just
part of the process.

07:02.804 --> 07:05.238
Would it make you feel better
if I told you

07:05.240 --> 07:09.175
that I have never felt more
proud of my future husband

07:09.227 --> 07:11.561
than I did watching you
up there today?

07:12.287 --> 07:15.822
Yes, it would.

07:15.857 --> 07:17.724
Good.

07:17.759 --> 07:19.475
Because I want to talk to you
about your closing.

07:19.527 --> 07:21.027
Ugh.

07:21.029 --> 07:23.162
Don't tell me you want me
to go with jury nullification.

07:23.214 --> 07:24.881
There is nothing wrong
with getting a jury

07:24.916 --> 07:26.849
to sympathize with you,
and, Mike, your parents died

07:26.885 --> 07:28.134
in a car accident.

07:28.169 --> 07:29.936
Who isn't gonna feel
for a person like that?

07:29.938 --> 07:31.404
Rachel, the only problem
with me saying,

07:31.456 --> 07:34.090
"Let me off because
tragedy struck me as a child"

07:34.125 --> 07:36.476
is I've pretty much admitted
that I'm guilty.

07:36.511 --> 07:38.845
No, the difference is that
that accident is the reason

07:38.847 --> 07:41.147
that you wanted to become
a lawyer in the first place.

07:41.149 --> 07:44.284
And they won't just understand
it, they will love you for it.

07:44.286 --> 07:47.387
How can you know that?

07:47.422 --> 07:50.823
Because I love you for it.

07:50.859 --> 07:54.160
Tell them your story
and I am telling you,

07:54.195 --> 07:56.129
they'll let you go.

07:56.164 --> 07:59.098
<i>[soft music]</i>

07:59.600 --> 08:02.234
<i>♪
♪</i>

08:02.270 --> 08:03.819
Louis, you wanted to see me?

08:03.871 --> 08:04.954
Yeah, that was hours ago.

08:04.989 --> 08:06.789
We need to talk.
We need to talk right now.

08:06.824 --> 08:08.140
- About what?
- About the fact that

08:08.176 --> 08:10.176
Mike Ross is all of a sudden
representing himself.

08:10.178 --> 08:11.877
And why exactly do we need
to talk about that?

08:11.913 --> 08:14.330
Because it means Harvey thinks
he's gonna lose.

08:14.365 --> 08:17.449
You wanna walk me
through that logic?

08:17.502 --> 08:19.952
Harvey's never given up
control of a case in his life,

08:19.987 --> 08:21.187
and if he's doing that now,

08:21.222 --> 08:22.788
it means he wants that loss
on Mike's record.

08:22.824 --> 08:23.904
Louis, at a time like this,

08:23.941 --> 08:25.858
Harvey doesn't care
about records.

08:25.893 --> 08:27.326
Bullshit.
I read the transcript

08:27.378 --> 08:29.628
backwards and forwards.
He thinks he's gonna lose.

08:29.630 --> 08:31.096
Louis, what's really
going on here?

08:31.132 --> 08:32.515
I'll tell you what's going on.

08:32.567 --> 08:33.732
If Harvey thinks
we're gonna lose,

08:33.768 --> 08:35.317
then we'll lose,
and if that happens,

08:35.352 --> 08:38.037
you know who Gibbs
is coming after next.

08:38.089 --> 08:42.006
Louis, we will deal with that
when and if she does,

08:42.009 --> 08:43.558
but I am telling you,

08:43.611 --> 08:47.496
Harvey letting Mike take
the reins is not him giving up.

08:47.532 --> 08:49.498
It's him growing up

08:49.550 --> 08:52.551
and realizing he is not
the one to bring this home.

08:53.103 --> 09:00.992
<i>♪
♪</i>

09:08.819 --> 09:10.669
Do you want to talk about it?

09:10.704 --> 09:12.704
Talk about what?

09:12.706 --> 09:14.039
Oh, I don't know,
maybe the fact

09:14.041 --> 09:16.091
that Mike is working
on a closing

09:16.126 --> 09:17.559
to keep himself out of jail

09:17.594 --> 09:19.811
and you're not working on it
with him.

09:19.863 --> 09:22.447
There's nothing for me to do,
Donna.

09:22.449 --> 09:23.915
It's in his hands.

09:23.917 --> 09:25.617
In his hands?

09:25.652 --> 09:27.102
Harvey,
that was a trial maneuver.

09:27.137 --> 09:28.887
It doesn't mean you can't
help him when he needs you.

09:28.889 --> 09:31.490
- He doesn't need me.
- He needs you more than ever.

09:31.525 --> 09:33.825
No, he doesn't,
and it's time for him

09:33.877 --> 09:35.794
to put the clipboard down
and get in the game.

09:35.796 --> 09:37.529
- Harvey--
- Donna, this wasn't just

09:37.564 --> 09:39.598
some move to slip testimony in.

09:39.600 --> 09:41.400
This is Mike's life.

09:41.402 --> 09:44.870
It's his story and he needs
to be the one to tell it.

09:44.872 --> 09:47.773
Everything he's done up until
now has prepared him for this,

09:47.808 --> 09:50.058
and I'm telling you,

09:50.110 --> 09:53.862
he's ready for it.

09:53.914 --> 09:56.047
<i>Is defense ready</i>
<i>for closing statements?</i>

09:56.583 --> 09:59.083
<i>♪
♪</i>

09:59.085 --> 10:01.002
Mike?

10:01.054 --> 10:02.487
You okay?

10:02.522 --> 10:05.023
Mr. Ross?

10:07.043 --> 10:09.327
Oh, uh, yes, Your Honor.

10:09.329 --> 10:17.235
<i>♪
♪</i>

10:18.838 --> 10:23.057
Um, ladies and gentleman
of the jury,

10:23.109 --> 10:25.743
I think most of us...

10:30.250 --> 10:32.216
[sighs]

10:32.269 --> 10:34.886
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:34.888 --> 10:36.921
You guys heard evidence earlier
in the trial

10:36.957 --> 10:39.157
that I have
a photographic memory,

10:39.209 --> 10:41.042
and I do,
but the way it works--

10:41.077 --> 10:43.745
I don't just take
a snapshot of something.

10:43.797 --> 10:45.013
See, I read it

10:45.065 --> 10:46.397
and then I understand it,

10:48.277 --> 10:49.735
and once I understand it,

10:49.835 --> 10:51.385
then I never forget it,

10:51.420 --> 10:53.937
but I've been trying
to memorize my speech,

10:53.973 --> 10:55.656
but I can't

10:55.691 --> 10:57.891
because it's bullshit,

10:57.927 --> 11:00.928
because I...

11:00.963 --> 11:03.297
I am bullshit.

11:03.299 --> 11:07.234
You see, the truth is--is that
I am guilty of being a fraud.

11:07.236 --> 11:09.536
My whole life I have wanted
to be a lawyer

11:09.538 --> 11:11.955
so that I could help people
like Clifford Danner.

11:12.007 --> 11:13.707
People who have no one else
to fight for them.

11:13.759 --> 11:15.976
No one who believes in them,

11:16.028 --> 11:18.529
but instead, all I've done
as a lawyer

11:18.564 --> 11:20.480
is work night and day

11:20.533 --> 11:23.333
to put money into the hands
of rich people.

11:23.385 --> 11:25.519
I was given a gift
and I wasted it,

11:25.554 --> 11:27.054
and I'm ashamed of myself.

11:27.106 --> 11:29.056
And--and as a final insult,

11:29.058 --> 11:31.859
I paraded this mourning woman
out in front of you

11:31.894 --> 11:34.828
just as a way
to get you to admire me.

11:34.830 --> 11:40.684
<i>♪
♪</i>

11:41.219 --> 11:43.236
I am so sorry, Gloria.

11:43.288 --> 11:44.821
- [mouthing]
- And all I can say is

11:44.873 --> 11:45.989
that I promise you,

11:46.041 --> 11:47.707
whether these people
find me innocent or not,

11:47.759 --> 11:50.009
I am gonna spend
the rest of my life

11:50.045 --> 11:54.347
fighting for the
Clifford Danners of this world.

11:54.349 --> 11:57.650
I will not waste
that gift again.

11:57.686 --> 12:01.171
<i>♪
♪</i>

12:01.706 --> 12:04.674
You could believe it or not,

12:04.726 --> 12:07.677
but I am a lawyer,

12:07.729 --> 12:09.512
and I always will be.

12:09.564 --> 12:11.847
<i>♪
♪</i>

12:11.900 --> 12:14.166
Thank you.

12:14.202 --> 12:22.174
<i>♪
♪</i>

12:24.646 --> 12:26.512
Well, it's an interesting
thing, really,

12:26.547 --> 12:29.615
how criminals can play
with our emotions.

12:29.651 --> 12:32.702
Mike Ross is articulate

12:32.754 --> 12:35.504
and persuasive and passionate

12:35.556 --> 12:37.056
and listening
to his closing argument,

12:37.091 --> 12:38.591
I almost want
to let him go myself,

12:38.643 --> 12:42.561
except for one thing:
He's a liar.

12:42.563 --> 12:45.147
He didn't commute to Harvard
one day a week

12:45.199 --> 12:46.732
as he so laughably claims.

12:46.784 --> 12:50.269
He didn't go to college.

12:50.305 --> 12:53.556
There is no paper record
of his enrollment,

12:53.608 --> 12:55.808
no applications to law school,

12:55.860 --> 12:57.693
no picture in the yearbook,

12:57.745 --> 12:59.111
no class rankings,

12:59.163 --> 13:03.082
no one at all
who even remembers him.

13:03.117 --> 13:05.785
Except for that
one indebted friend

13:05.820 --> 13:06.919
with a lot to lose,

13:06.921 --> 13:08.754
and if you believe
his testimony,

13:08.756 --> 13:12.224
I got a bridge over Brooklyn
I'd like to sell you.

13:12.226 --> 13:15.111
And whether he says it or not,

13:15.163 --> 13:17.196
he's banking on the fact

13:17.248 --> 13:21.167
that you are gonna think
this is a victimless crime,

13:21.202 --> 13:23.135
but if you acquit him,

13:23.187 --> 13:25.655
you are giving permission
to everyone to say...

13:25.690 --> 13:26.822
[voices reverberating]
"Hey, I'm gonna pretend

13:26.858 --> 13:28.190
"to be a lawyer.

13:28.242 --> 13:29.942
"I think I'm gonna say
I'm a doctor.

13:29.994 --> 13:31.110
"Hell, you know what?

13:31.162 --> 13:34.547
Today,
I'm gonna pose as a pilot."

13:34.582 --> 13:37.767
Imagine if one day you woke up
on the operating table

13:37.802 --> 13:41.904
to discover the man who was
about to crack open your chest

13:41.939 --> 13:44.457
is not really a doctor.

13:44.492 --> 13:46.959
Guilty.

13:46.995 --> 13:49.712
Guilty.

13:49.747 --> 13:51.630
Guilty.

13:51.666 --> 13:53.399
Make no mistake about it,

13:53.434 --> 13:55.434
Mike Ross thinks
he's better than you.

13:55.486 --> 13:57.570
He thinks he doesn't have
to play by the same rules,

13:57.622 --> 14:01.123
but we know he does

14:01.159 --> 14:03.242
because, ladies and gentleman
of the jury,

14:03.277 --> 14:05.628
Mike Ross...

14:05.680 --> 14:07.797
<i>[dark music]</i>

14:07.849 --> 14:11.133
Is a fraud.

14:11.185 --> 14:15.971
<i>♪
♪</i>

14:16.024 --> 14:18.057
Mike...

14:18.109 --> 14:21.193
Mike...

14:21.245 --> 14:22.361
[voices return to normal]
Mike.

14:22.413 --> 14:24.163
She was good, Harvey.

14:24.165 --> 14:25.831
- Yeah, so were you.
- You were great.

14:25.883 --> 14:28.300
She was better.
Everything she said was true

14:28.336 --> 14:29.418
and the jury knows it.

14:29.470 --> 14:30.970
No they don't.

14:31.022 --> 14:34.023
Look, ever since
the day I met you,

14:34.058 --> 14:35.691
you have always seen
the good in people,

14:35.727 --> 14:37.860
and we only need one person
on the jury

14:37.895 --> 14:39.245
to feel that way about you.

14:39.280 --> 14:40.913
- And what if they don't?
- It doesn't matter

14:40.948 --> 14:42.665
because we can't do anything
about it anyways.

14:42.700 --> 14:43.949
So, let's get out of here.

14:43.951 --> 14:45.511
- I can't.
- What do you mean you can't?

14:45.536 --> 14:48.120
I mean, I can't leave
until that jury comes back.

14:48.172 --> 14:49.839
Mike, they might not come back
for days.

14:49.874 --> 14:52.258
I don't know what to tell you,
Harvey, but I can't leave here.

14:52.293 --> 14:54.260
It's okay, Harvey.

14:54.295 --> 14:57.263
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:57.298 --> 14:58.798
<i>♪
♪</i>

14:58.800 --> 15:00.966
Look,

15:00.968 --> 15:02.802
Mike, if we really
don't have time,

15:02.804 --> 15:04.353
I don't want to waste it here.

15:04.389 --> 15:05.638
Rachel, if I leave,

15:05.640 --> 15:06.806
all I'm gonna be thinking about

15:06.858 --> 15:08.974
is what's happening
in that jury room.

15:09.026 --> 15:11.227
Then I am going to go
and get us some food

15:11.279 --> 15:13.562
and we're gonna have
a bite to eat

15:13.614 --> 15:16.148
because I'm not gonna
let this time go to waste.

15:17.584 --> 15:18.584
Okay.

15:18.608 --> 15:21.608
<i>♪
♪</i>

15:23.000 --> 15:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

15:33.503 --> 15:35.220
[indistinct chatter]

15:36.857 --> 15:39.191
- What?
- What do you mean what?

15:39.193 --> 15:41.326
I want to know what you think.

15:41.362 --> 15:43.195
I think I saw
a heavyweight fight

15:43.247 --> 15:45.030
that's gonna come down
to the goddamn cards.

15:45.065 --> 15:46.181
You see it any different?

15:46.217 --> 15:48.000
What I see is my fate
in the hands of a jury,

15:48.035 --> 15:49.568
and I don't like it.
Why the hell do you think

15:49.603 --> 15:51.453
I cut so many deals
instead of going to trial?

15:51.488 --> 15:53.605
Well, the only deal
that Gibbs is going to cut

15:53.641 --> 15:55.424
is the one that
hangs us out to dry.

15:55.459 --> 15:56.975
And I don't know about you,

15:57.011 --> 15:58.577
but I don't feel like
just sitting by

15:58.612 --> 16:00.145
while this thing goes
to verdict.

16:00.197 --> 16:01.647
You think I do?

16:01.649 --> 16:03.982
Look, there's no other w--

16:03.984 --> 16:06.368
<i>[soft music]</i>

16:06.920 --> 16:08.787
Hold on a second.

16:08.789 --> 16:10.522
We could go get us a mistrial.

16:10.557 --> 16:11.723
What good would that do?

16:11.758 --> 16:14.259
A mistrial's just gonna
kick the can down the road

16:14.294 --> 16:15.577
till Mike gets tried again.

16:15.612 --> 16:16.661
Listen to me.

16:16.696 --> 16:18.046
When Mike wanted to
represent himself,

16:18.081 --> 16:19.464
Gibbs jumped out of her chair

16:19.499 --> 16:21.349
saying that we were trying
to get a mistrial.

16:21.384 --> 16:24.969
Then she demanded we waive
our rights to one completely.

16:25.005 --> 16:26.654
And the only reason
she'd do that

16:26.706 --> 16:28.490
is because she doesn't
have authorization

16:28.542 --> 16:30.658
to try this case again.
Which means,

16:30.710 --> 16:33.011
a mistrial isn't just
kicking the can down the road.

16:33.063 --> 16:35.680
No, it's blowing it
to kingdom come.

16:35.682 --> 16:36.865
<i>♪
♪</i>

16:37.400 --> 16:38.516
The only problem is,

16:38.551 --> 16:40.201
we don't have grounds
for a mistrial.

16:40.253 --> 16:42.637
Well, then you better go out
and find some.

16:42.672 --> 16:46.023
And you better do it
before that jury comes back.

16:46.059 --> 16:49.026
<i>♪
♪</i>

16:49.078 --> 16:50.444
That's what I'm trying
to tell you.

16:50.496 --> 16:51.662
My lawyer's not here.

16:51.698 --> 16:52.997
That's not my problem.

16:53.032 --> 16:54.131
Then why did he tell me that

16:54.133 --> 16:55.549
if I told you
he couldn't make it,

16:55.601 --> 16:57.201
you'd give me a continuance
or something?

16:57.236 --> 16:59.270
I'll tell you what I'll do,
Mr. Diaz.

16:59.322 --> 17:00.538
Since Perkins isn't here,

17:00.573 --> 17:01.956
I'll help you out.

17:01.991 --> 17:03.207
Instead of going to trial
and winding up

17:03.259 --> 17:04.425
with a five year sentence,

17:04.460 --> 17:06.894
I'll let you cop
to three and a half right here.

17:07.074 --> 17:08.324
Five years?

17:08.358 --> 17:09.959
We stole some TVs.

17:10.011 --> 17:11.727
For the third time,
and that's five years.

17:11.762 --> 17:13.262
I was only driving the car,
man.

17:13.263 --> 17:15.314
Then you can drive yourself
to prison, man,

17:15.366 --> 17:16.699
but I'm not giving you
a continuance.

17:16.733 --> 17:18.117
Hey, I'm sorry to interrupt,

17:18.169 --> 17:20.502
but he doesn't give you
a continuance, the judge does.

17:20.505 --> 17:21.971
And you're entitled
to one automatically

17:22.006 --> 17:23.521
if this is the first time
your attorney didn't show.

17:23.558 --> 17:26.075
- And who the hell are you?
-That's not your concern.

17:26.109 --> 17:27.159
And this is not your concern.

17:27.194 --> 17:28.596
Yeah, well,
I'm making it my concern

17:28.629 --> 17:30.079
since I don't like
watching prosecutors

17:30.131 --> 17:31.964
take advantage
of unrepresented defendants.

17:32.339 --> 17:34.039
All I'm doing is
offering the man a deal.

17:34.074 --> 17:35.757
I'm not taking advantage.
That is bullshit.

17:35.809 --> 17:37.569
You know full well
his lawyer didn't tell him

17:37.611 --> 17:38.977
to ask you for a continuance.

17:39.029 --> 17:40.529
He told him
to ask the judge for one.

17:40.581 --> 17:42.664
Now you're gonna try and bully
him into three and a half years

17:42.716 --> 17:44.836
for what sounds to me like
a simple misdemeanor theft.

17:44.885 --> 17:46.852
You don't know shit
about this case.

17:46.887 --> 17:48.687
Well, I'm about to.
Hand over the case file.

17:48.739 --> 17:49.905
I don't have
to give you anything.

17:49.940 --> 17:51.406
You're not his attorney.

17:51.458 --> 17:53.291
Mr. Diaz,
my name is Mike Ross.

17:53.327 --> 17:54.543
Now, do you want me
to represent you

17:54.595 --> 17:56.194
or do you want to stick
with this asshole Perkins

17:56.230 --> 17:59.347
who didn't even show up
to your hearing?

17:59.399 --> 18:00.899
He's my lawyer.

18:05.128 --> 18:08.096
Donna, I need your help
and I need it right now.

18:08.131 --> 18:09.597
What's going on?
Is the jury back?

18:09.633 --> 18:11.983
No, I need to know
if Stephanie Liston still works

18:12.035 --> 18:14.118
at the U .S. Attorney's Office.
She does, why?

18:14.120 --> 18:15.620
I need the names
of the jurors.

18:15.622 --> 18:17.005
Harvey, if you're even
thinking about tampering--

18:17.057 --> 18:19.390
No, I'm not thinking
of tampering with the jury.

18:19.426 --> 18:21.226
I just need to find grounds
for a mistrial.

18:21.278 --> 18:22.694
A mistrial?

18:22.696 --> 18:24.412
You told Mike he killed it.
Was that a lie?

18:24.447 --> 18:25.807
- No, it wasn't.
- Then why are you

18:25.832 --> 18:27.966
so suddenly having doubts?
It's called hedging.

18:28.001 --> 18:29.133
No, it is called
breaking the law

18:29.186 --> 18:30.351
and I don't want any part of it.

18:30.387 --> 18:32.770
Goddamn it, Donna.
I'm trying to protect Mike.

18:33.197 --> 18:35.398
Then maybe you should be
getting a mistrial legally

18:35.450 --> 18:37.116
instead of having me do
what you're asking.

18:37.151 --> 18:39.085
- We don't have time.
- I don't care!

18:39.087 --> 18:40.219
What the hell's wrong
with you?

18:40.255 --> 18:41.420
- Me?
- Yes, you.

18:41.422 --> 18:43.222
Whose side are you on?
Oh, don't you dare

18:43.274 --> 18:44.907
ask me that.
You know damn well

18:44.943 --> 18:46.692
that I would break the law
for you and Mike,

18:46.728 --> 18:48.044
but you are asking me

18:48.079 --> 18:49.245
to have my friend do it,

18:49.297 --> 18:50.863
and I am not going to.
Donna--

18:50.898 --> 18:52.598
Harvey,
even if I did ask Stephanie

18:52.600 --> 18:54.600
and she said yes,
which she never would,

18:54.636 --> 18:56.569
you would have
to drag innocent people

18:56.571 --> 18:58.454
through the mud
to get this done.

18:58.712 --> 19:00.378
And the Harvey I know

19:00.414 --> 19:02.380
isn't that kind of person.

19:02.382 --> 19:05.350
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:05.352 --> 19:13.325
<i>♪
♪</i>

19:15.861 --> 19:17.310
Donna, what is going on?

19:17.363 --> 19:18.979
Why are you so upset?
I'm not upset.

19:19.031 --> 19:20.947
[sighs]
When you say, "I'm not upset,"

19:21.000 --> 19:23.750
is that you acting?
Because it sucks.

19:23.802 --> 19:25.252
What do you want
from me, Louis?

19:25.287 --> 19:27.354
I want you to cut the bullshit
and tell me what's wrong.

19:27.389 --> 19:28.605
I just saw you
leave Harvey's office

19:28.640 --> 19:30.524
and five seconds later,
I saw him do the same thing.

19:30.576 --> 19:32.442
Okay, Louis, what's wrong is
Harvey wants me

19:32.494 --> 19:33.827
to get the names of the jurors
from my friend

19:33.879 --> 19:35.328
in the U.S. Attorney's Office.

19:35.330 --> 19:37.464
- He's trying to tamper?
- He's trying to get a mistrial.

19:37.499 --> 19:39.049
Well, then why the hell
aren't you helping him do it?

19:39.101 --> 19:40.350
- What?
- You heard me.

19:40.386 --> 19:42.102
Why aren't you doing
whatever you can do help him?

19:42.137 --> 19:43.570
I can't believe
you just said that to me.

19:43.605 --> 19:45.355
Donna, listen to me,
if Harvey's doing this,

19:45.407 --> 19:47.157
it means he thinks
he's going to lose.

19:47.209 --> 19:48.492
And if he thinks
he's gonna lose,

19:48.544 --> 19:49.743
it means he is gonna lose.

19:49.795 --> 19:50.911
And if Mike goes down,

19:50.946 --> 19:52.546
everybody goes down with him.

19:52.548 --> 19:53.797
Don't you care
about that at all?

19:53.849 --> 19:55.432
I'm getting a little tired
of people asking me

19:55.484 --> 19:57.184
whether I care or not.
Because I do,

19:57.186 --> 19:59.102
but not enough to push
women and children aside

19:59.154 --> 20:00.487
to get on a lifeboat.

20:00.522 --> 20:02.572
So, if that's all you came
in here to ask me,

20:02.624 --> 20:04.541
why don't you be on your way?

20:04.576 --> 20:11.098
<i>♪
♪</i>

20:11.573 --> 20:15.124
Okay, I got us some bread,

20:15.159 --> 20:17.760
cheese, a little bit of wine,
and a picnic blanket.

20:17.812 --> 20:19.896
So, I feel like we should
just go outside--

20:19.931 --> 20:21.731
- I can't.
- What do you mean you can't?

20:21.783 --> 20:22.899
Did the jury come back?

20:22.951 --> 20:24.984
No, I, uh, I met a defendant.

20:25.036 --> 20:27.453
He got caught in the act
of some petty larceny,

20:27.505 --> 20:29.655
and, uh, they're trying
to railroad him, so I--

20:29.691 --> 20:31.140
So, you're taking a case?

20:31.175 --> 20:32.491
Rachel, he tried
to sell a couple of TVs

20:32.527 --> 20:34.610
out of the back of a truck.
Now he's facing five years.

20:34.646 --> 20:36.279
And somewhere in this building
there are 12 people

20:36.314 --> 20:37.813
deciding whether or not
you're a fraud

20:37.865 --> 20:40.199
and you're sitting here doing
the exact thing

20:40.251 --> 20:41.450
that they're accusing you of.

20:41.502 --> 20:42.501
They were right
in front of me.

20:42.537 --> 20:43.836
His lawyer didn't show up--

20:43.838 --> 20:45.555
- What is wrong with you?
- Whoa, Rachel, hey--

20:45.590 --> 20:48.524
Don't you understand
that I am scared,

20:48.560 --> 20:50.276
and that I am trying
to be supportive

20:50.311 --> 20:51.527
and to keep a brave face,

20:51.563 --> 20:53.246
but that I could lose you, Mike?

20:53.281 --> 20:55.214
So, I understand
you wanting to be here,

20:55.250 --> 20:58.050
but I don't understand you
not wanting to be with me.

20:58.086 --> 20:59.885
<i>♪
♪</i>

21:00.110 --> 21:02.444
Come here.

21:02.446 --> 21:07.483
<i>♪
♪</i>

21:07.518 --> 21:09.301
Look, I'm scared too.

21:09.353 --> 21:10.853
That's why I can't go home.

21:10.888 --> 21:13.889
And I don't know
how I got into this, but...

21:15.359 --> 21:18.110
I know that I need to do this,
Rachel.

21:18.162 --> 21:20.996
<i>♪
♪</i>

21:21.397 --> 21:24.866
You really meant what you said
to the jury, didn't you?

21:24.901 --> 21:26.367
Yeah.

21:26.402 --> 21:27.919
And you said that
you fell in love with me

21:27.954 --> 21:29.634
because of me wanting
to help other people.

21:29.672 --> 21:32.006
Well, this guy needs my help.

21:34.928 --> 21:37.929
And it may be the last time
I can do something like this.

21:39.515 --> 21:42.350
Well, then let's figure out
a way to help him together.

21:42.352 --> 21:48.322
<i>♪
♪</i>

21:54.080 --> 21:56.047
What's for lunch, David?

21:56.082 --> 21:57.715
Quinoa salad.

21:57.750 --> 21:59.267
Well, enjoy it,

21:59.302 --> 22:00.601
because it's gonna be
your last meal

22:00.637 --> 22:01.769
as a U.S. Attorney.

22:01.804 --> 22:03.471
Mike Ross promised me

22:03.473 --> 22:04.855
that if I gave him
those phone records,

22:04.891 --> 22:06.641
he wouldn't say anything
to anyone.

22:06.643 --> 22:08.109
I'm not Mike Ross,

22:08.144 --> 22:10.561
and the way I see it,

22:10.613 --> 22:12.730
there's no reason
for me not to tell Gibbs

22:12.782 --> 22:14.448
about your shady past

22:14.484 --> 22:15.950
unless you give me a reason.

22:15.985 --> 22:17.868
And how am I supposed
to do that?

22:17.904 --> 22:19.370
You pack up your lunch,

22:19.405 --> 22:21.956
you take it down the street
to the courthouse cafe,

22:21.991 --> 22:24.492
and you share a table
with whatever juror shows up

22:24.544 --> 22:27.712
when they break for coffee
in about two hours.

22:28.798 --> 22:30.081
What's this for?

22:30.133 --> 22:33.134
For when you buy juror number
whatever a cup of coffee.

22:33.169 --> 22:36.337
Jesus Christ, you want me
to give you a mistrial?

22:36.339 --> 22:38.422
I do that, I could lose my job.

22:38.474 --> 22:41.008
You're gonna lose your freedom
in two hours if you don't.

22:41.010 --> 22:43.477
This is blackmail.

22:43.513 --> 22:45.146
I call it atonement,

22:45.181 --> 22:48.649
and today's the day
you face the music.

22:48.685 --> 22:54.021
<i>♪
♪</i>

22:58.950 --> 23:01.318
- You were right.
<i>- About what?</i>

23:01.370 --> 23:03.370
I shouldn't have been willing
to hurt innocent people

23:03.405 --> 23:05.338
<i>to get done</i>
<i>what I needed to get done.</i>

23:05.866 --> 23:07.883
Well, it sounds like
you got it done anyway.

23:07.917 --> 23:10.468
<i>I did, and you're gonna get</i>
<i>a call from Vanessa</i>

23:10.470 --> 23:12.303
as soon as she gets me
some pictures I need.

23:12.513 --> 23:14.129
Harvey, you just said that you
shouldn't have been willing

23:14.165 --> 23:15.464
to hurt innocent people, and--

23:15.500 --> 23:17.366
<i>I didn't hurt</i>
<i>any innocent people, Donna.</i>

23:17.401 --> 23:18.534
I found a guilty one.

23:18.569 --> 23:19.819
<i>Well, then I will</i>
<i>go tell Jessica</i>

23:19.871 --> 23:21.670
and I will let you know
the second Vanessa calls.

23:21.722 --> 23:24.306
<i>Donna.</i>

23:24.342 --> 23:25.808
What, Harvey?

23:25.810 --> 23:27.810
Thanks.

23:27.862 --> 23:31.247
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:31.352 --> 23:32.902
I can't believe we found that.

23:32.954 --> 23:34.236
I can't believe you did.

23:34.288 --> 23:35.988
Rachel, this might give us
the leverage

23:35.990 --> 23:37.840
to make sure Diaz doesn't do
any jail time at all.

23:37.892 --> 23:39.725
- Do you really think so?
- Yeah, I do.

23:39.727 --> 23:41.694
And it doesn't surprise me

23:41.729 --> 23:43.913
'cause I also think that you're
gonna make a great lawyer.

23:43.948 --> 23:45.397
Well, then spending our time
doing this

23:45.433 --> 23:47.383
wasn't such a bad idea
after all.

23:47.418 --> 23:49.635
Mr. Diaz, are you ready
to enter a plea?

23:49.687 --> 23:51.904
Before we do, Your Honor,
I'd like to enter a motion

23:51.939 --> 23:54.073
to invalidate the search
of Mr. Diaz's vehicle.

23:54.075 --> 23:55.624
- What?
- The warrant was obtained

23:55.660 --> 23:58.377
because of a phone call between
my client and his cousin,

23:58.379 --> 24:00.930
and there's no evidence that
Mr. Alexander had authorization

24:00.982 --> 24:02.214
to tap that call.
Your Honor,

24:02.249 --> 24:03.816
we had other sources
for our search warrant.

24:03.868 --> 24:05.951
- And what exactly were they?
- Mr. Alexander?

24:05.953 --> 24:08.170
Objection, Your Honor.

24:08.692 --> 24:10.559
Ms. Gibbs, this case isn't

24:10.611 --> 24:12.861
under the Justice Department's
jurisdiction,

24:12.863 --> 24:15.213
so, what exactly
are you objecting to?

24:15.249 --> 24:17.549
I'm objecting to the fact
that this man is not a lawyer.

24:17.601 --> 24:18.767
Your Honor, that is a lie.

24:18.802 --> 24:20.936
And as we speak,
a jury is finding him guilty.

24:20.988 --> 24:22.704
And until they do,
my bar number is active.

24:22.739 --> 24:23.955
This is ridiculous,
Your Honor.

24:23.991 --> 24:26.057
He is making a mockery
of this entire courtroom,

24:26.109 --> 24:28.443
and I urge you
to at least delay this case

24:28.478 --> 24:29.945
until his jury comes back.

24:29.997 --> 24:31.947
Your Honor, the only reason
I'm representing Mr. Diaz,

24:31.999 --> 24:33.915
is because his court-appointed
lawyer didn't show up,

24:33.917 --> 24:35.750
and then that man attempted
to railroad him

24:35.752 --> 24:37.118
into an outrageous plea deal.

24:37.154 --> 24:40.055
Ms. Gibbs, he may be a fraud
in your court,

24:40.057 --> 24:42.524
but since he hasn't been
convicted of anything,

24:42.526 --> 24:43.992
he isn't one in mine.

24:44.027 --> 24:47.329
And unless Mr. Alexander here
magically finds his voice,

24:47.381 --> 24:48.663
Mr. Ross's motion

24:48.715 --> 24:52.634
to exclude the search
of his clients vehicle passes.

24:52.686 --> 24:56.321
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:56.819 --> 24:59.086
Is it true
what that woman was saying?

24:59.122 --> 25:01.005
Yes, they're deliberating
on his fate right now.

25:01.040 --> 25:02.707
I don't give a shit
if they're deliberating.

25:02.742 --> 25:04.141
Is he a fake or not?

25:04.177 --> 25:06.093
You saw what he just did,
and he's about to cut you a deal

25:06.145 --> 25:08.145
from four years behind bars
to maybe a few months.

25:08.197 --> 25:10.147
So what do you think?

25:10.149 --> 25:11.615
<i>♪
♪</i>

25:11.705 --> 25:12.871
What'd he say?

25:12.906 --> 25:14.506
He's too pissed off
to make a deal right now,

25:14.558 --> 25:17.142
but trust me, he'll calm down,
and then he will.

25:17.144 --> 25:18.643
Mike, where are you going?

25:18.695 --> 25:21.312
I'm gonna go try
and make a deal of my own.

25:21.314 --> 25:28.586
<i>♪
♪</i>

25:29.639 --> 25:31.005
You ran out of there so fast

25:31.057 --> 25:33.658
I didn't get a chance
to talk to you.

25:33.693 --> 25:36.277
What exactly do you want,
Mr. Ross?

25:36.329 --> 25:40.215
I want to make a deal.

25:40.250 --> 25:42.000
You finally ready
to turn on Mr. Specter?

25:42.052 --> 25:44.552
Nope, but I am ready
to plead guilty

25:44.604 --> 25:46.971
and never practice law again

25:46.973 --> 25:48.356
if you agree

25:48.391 --> 25:50.909
to not go after any of
the partners at Person Specter.

25:50.911 --> 25:52.544
That's the same bullshit
your boss said to me

25:52.579 --> 25:53.745
when I first met him.

25:53.780 --> 25:54.879
You're done practicing,

25:54.881 --> 25:57.132
so I should just let you
get away with it?

25:57.184 --> 25:58.983
Why would I listen to you now

25:59.019 --> 26:00.518
if I didn't listen to him then?

26:00.520 --> 26:04.455
Because you've got it written
all over your face.

26:04.491 --> 26:07.125
Seeing me be a lawyer
makes you sick.

26:07.127 --> 26:08.293
Right?
And if I win,

26:08.295 --> 26:09.677
I'm gonna keep being a lawyer,

26:09.713 --> 26:11.763
and it's gonna make you sick
for the rest of your life.

26:11.815 --> 26:14.983
No deal.
It's not a good enough reason.

26:15.018 --> 26:16.818
Okay, then let's try this one.

26:16.853 --> 26:19.103
You've been at the same level
at the U.S. Attorney's Office

26:19.105 --> 26:20.238
for a long time.

26:20.749 --> 26:22.165
Now, a person
who can't get a conviction

26:22.217 --> 26:24.934
against a man that
everyone thinks is a fraud,

26:24.970 --> 26:26.469
well, that's a person
who's going nowhere.

26:26.471 --> 26:28.972
This is a chance
for you to save face.

26:29.358 --> 26:31.125
I don't need to save face

26:31.127 --> 26:32.676
because they're gonna
find you guilty.

26:32.712 --> 26:34.428
Are you sure about that?

26:34.430 --> 26:37.014
'Cause you couldn't convince one
judge to make me stand down,

26:37.066 --> 26:40.451
so what makes you think
you're gonna convince 12 jurors?

26:40.486 --> 26:42.036
You know what, Mike?

26:42.071 --> 26:43.170
The truth is,

26:43.205 --> 26:45.089
you would have made
a good lawyer,

26:45.124 --> 26:46.874
but you're not one,

26:46.926 --> 26:48.892
and I'm gonna put you away.

26:48.928 --> 26:55.149
<i>♪
♪</i>

26:55.151 --> 26:56.784
- What can I do for you, Donna?
- Harvey wanted me

26:56.836 --> 26:58.202
to let you know
that as long as they don't

26:58.254 --> 26:59.553
reach a verdict
in the next few hours,

26:59.588 --> 27:02.222
you'll have a mistrial.
I'll have a mistrial?

27:02.258 --> 27:04.108
What's on your mind, Donna?
Nothing.

27:04.143 --> 27:06.026
I guess I just never thought
I'd see the day

27:06.062 --> 27:07.644
when you thought
Harvey was gonna lose.

27:07.697 --> 27:09.463
And who says
I think Harvey's going to lose?

27:09.498 --> 27:10.864
- A mistrial says it.
- No,

27:10.900 --> 27:12.366
it says I'm not willing
to take a chance

27:12.368 --> 27:13.834
on 12 complete strangers.

27:13.869 --> 27:15.202
It says you don't have faith
in him.

27:15.204 --> 27:16.587
Donna, you don't know
what you're saying.

27:16.622 --> 27:18.088
Don't I?
I know I'm not a lawyer,

27:18.124 --> 27:20.507
but isn't it true that
if Mike gets found innocent,

27:20.509 --> 27:23.510
there's no double jeopardy,
but if a mistrial happens,

27:23.512 --> 27:25.846
they might come after him again
one day?

27:25.848 --> 27:28.482
Yes, Donna, that is true,

27:28.484 --> 27:31.151
but Harvey and I are banking
that never happens.

27:31.203 --> 27:32.953
- And what if it does?
- Then I'm sorry,

27:32.988 --> 27:34.988
but the truth is,
Mike Ross is the reason

27:34.990 --> 27:36.757
why we're in this mess
in the first place,

27:36.792 --> 27:37.925
and if it's a choice

27:37.960 --> 27:39.877
between his peace of mind
down the road

27:39.929 --> 27:41.178
and mine today,

27:41.213 --> 27:43.764
I'm choosing mine.

27:43.799 --> 27:46.400
Now, is that all?

27:46.435 --> 27:54.341
<i>♪
♪</i>

27:54.376 --> 27:56.543
[keyboard clacking]

27:56.579 --> 27:58.128
Louis Litt,
what a coincidence,

27:58.164 --> 28:00.714
I was just about to call your
office, say I was your cousin,

28:00.750 --> 28:02.966
and ask if you'd decided
to take me up on my offer.

28:03.002 --> 28:04.685
Before I give you an answer,
I want to know,

28:04.720 --> 28:06.386
if I give you proof
that Harvey knew about Mike,

28:06.439 --> 28:09.473
will you give me immunity?
Well, that depends.

28:09.525 --> 28:10.624
What do you have?

28:10.659 --> 28:11.775
What do you mean,
what do I have?

28:11.827 --> 28:12.943
I have me.

28:12.995 --> 28:14.244
Well, that's not good enough.

28:14.280 --> 28:15.863
Well, then what the hell
did you come to me for?

28:15.915 --> 28:17.431
Because I was expecting
something more

28:17.466 --> 28:20.000
than the testimony of a man
who's saving his own ass,

28:20.035 --> 28:21.418
which gets me nothing.

28:21.454 --> 28:23.170
Nothing?
I'd be giving you my word.

28:23.205 --> 28:25.839
And I don't need your word.
I need proof.

28:25.875 --> 28:27.341
Well, goddamn it,
I don't have any proof.

28:27.376 --> 28:28.759
Well, then you're no good
to me.

28:28.794 --> 28:31.545
And now I'm in the position of
having to work that much harder

28:31.597 --> 28:33.347
to get both you
and your partners,

28:33.382 --> 28:36.767
so, if you'll excuse me,
I need to get back to it, Louis.

28:36.802 --> 28:43.774
<i>♪
♪</i>

28:43.809 --> 28:45.476
Donna, I need you
to start prepping a motion

28:45.528 --> 28:47.945
for Mike to ask for a mistrial,

28:47.980 --> 28:49.897
and we're gonna need to do it
first thing in the morning.

28:49.949 --> 28:51.698
Harvey, I don't think
there's gonna be a mistrial.

28:51.734 --> 28:52.866
What the hell
are you talking about?

28:52.902 --> 28:54.701
I just got off the phone
with Vanessa.

28:54.737 --> 28:57.404
David Green never showed.

28:57.456 --> 28:59.790
<i>♪
♪</i>

29:08.144 --> 29:09.478
Whatever it is, Louis,

29:09.808 --> 29:10.924
I don't have the time.

29:10.959 --> 29:12.159
Well, you better find the time

29:12.194 --> 29:13.760
because Anita Gibbs
just offered me a deal.

29:13.795 --> 29:16.246
And I assume you told her
to shove it up her ass.

29:16.281 --> 29:17.998
I did, but what I really
wanted to say was,

29:18.000 --> 29:20.133
"Where do I sign?"

29:20.185 --> 29:21.634
What the hell
did you just say to me?

29:21.973 --> 29:23.589
Did you ever think
for one second,

29:23.591 --> 29:25.324
what's gonna happen
if Mike gets convicted?

29:25.359 --> 29:27.242
Mike is not gonna
get convicted.

29:27.278 --> 29:29.211
- How could you be so sure?
- Because I'm gonna go get us

29:29.246 --> 29:31.263
a goddamn mistrial.
That's not good enough.

29:31.299 --> 29:32.798
I want to know
how you're gonna do that.

29:32.850 --> 29:34.550
- None of your business.
- It is my business.

29:34.602 --> 29:36.235
If you're gonna go
and break some more laws

29:36.270 --> 29:38.339
like you did when you hired
the fraud in the first place.

29:38.340 --> 29:39.639
What the hell do you want,
Louis?

29:39.675 --> 29:41.007
You want me to give you
permission to cut a deal?

29:41.060 --> 29:42.442
I want you
to give yourself up.

29:42.478 --> 29:45.312
- Are you out of your mind?
- No, I am <i>in</i> my mind.

29:45.347 --> 29:47.267
You can't get a mistrial,
that verdict comes back

29:47.299 --> 29:48.415
the wrong way,

29:48.450 --> 29:50.217
everyone in this entire firm
goes to jail

29:50.252 --> 29:51.351
because of what you did.

29:51.353 --> 29:52.519
- Go home, Louis.
- No, no, no,

29:52.521 --> 29:53.687
I want you to say it.

29:53.739 --> 29:55.155
You went out on your own,
you hired a fraud,

29:55.207 --> 29:56.323
and this whole firm's
paying for it.

29:56.325 --> 29:57.924
- Shut the hell up.
- You and you alone

29:57.960 --> 29:59.793
are responsible for the carnage
of what's to come.

29:59.845 --> 30:01.812
- Louis--
- Just say it!

30:01.847 --> 30:04.231
You listen to me.
I may have hired a fraud,

30:04.233 --> 30:06.450
but you're the one who had
the chance to turn him in

30:06.485 --> 30:09.719
and you used his secret
to get what you always wanted.

30:09.755 --> 30:11.338
So, don't come here
at the 11th hour

30:11.373 --> 30:13.473
trying to blame me for having
to sleep in the bed

30:13.509 --> 30:16.643
that you made.

30:17.056 --> 30:19.173
I don't want to go to prison,
Harvey.

30:19.209 --> 30:21.809
Then get out of my way,
and let me do what I do.

30:21.845 --> 30:24.779
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:24.814 --> 30:32.753
<i>♪
♪</i>

30:34.557 --> 30:35.923
[beeps]

30:35.975 --> 30:42.413
<i>♪
♪</i>

30:42.415 --> 30:43.881
What are you doing here?

30:43.883 --> 30:46.350
I came to talk.

30:50.156 --> 30:52.156
I gotta hand it to you,

30:52.192 --> 30:53.724
you would have made
a good lawyer,

30:53.760 --> 30:55.726
but you're even better
than I gave you credit for.

30:55.762 --> 30:57.562
You got in my head.

30:57.614 --> 30:59.313
You came here
to take my offer?

30:59.365 --> 31:01.616
I came to make an offer
of my own.

31:01.668 --> 31:03.301
You said you were giving me
a chance to save face,

31:03.336 --> 31:06.304
but I let you get off
with no punishment.

31:06.356 --> 31:08.105
As far as my career goes,

31:08.141 --> 31:10.241
I might as well have
let them find you innocent.

31:10.718 --> 31:11.984
What do you want?

31:12.020 --> 31:14.220
You plead guilty,
do two years in prison,

31:14.255 --> 31:15.821
and I won't go after
any of your friends.

31:15.823 --> 31:17.289
There's no way
I agree to prison time

31:17.325 --> 31:18.457
for a crime I didn't commit.

31:18.459 --> 31:19.875
We're not in the courtroom
right now, Mike,

31:19.927 --> 31:21.060
so let's cut the bullshit.

31:21.095 --> 31:22.762
We both know you did this.

31:22.797 --> 31:24.280
So if you don't want to pay,

31:24.315 --> 31:25.631
then you take me up
on my original offer.

31:25.667 --> 31:27.033
You do no time,

31:27.085 --> 31:30.136
and all I need in return is
one name partner at your firm.

31:30.171 --> 31:32.054
And I told you
that's never gonna happen.

31:32.106 --> 31:34.306
[floor board creaks]

31:34.731 --> 31:36.597
Well, maybe you want
to talk to your fiancé

31:36.633 --> 31:38.166
because the look
on her face says

31:38.201 --> 31:40.001
she'd rather throw one of them
to the wolves

31:40.036 --> 31:41.819
then see you in prison.

31:41.855 --> 31:43.037
So it's up to you.

31:43.073 --> 31:44.806
You take either one of my deals,

31:44.841 --> 31:47.208
or you take your chances
with the jury.

31:47.243 --> 31:48.376
Just remember,

31:48.411 --> 31:50.511
tick tock.

31:50.563 --> 31:55.400
<i>♪
♪</i>

31:55.752 --> 31:58.669
[door opens and closes]

31:58.705 --> 32:01.389
What did she mean,
"either deal"?

32:01.424 --> 32:03.824
<i>♪
♪</i>

32:03.876 --> 32:05.242
She countered my offer.

32:05.294 --> 32:06.377
- How long?
- Rachel--

32:06.429 --> 32:07.962
How long would you have
to be away for?

32:08.014 --> 32:09.597
- Two years.
- No, Mike.

32:09.632 --> 32:10.831
No, you can't.
Do you know

32:10.867 --> 32:12.366
how much time I'm facing
if I'm found guilty?

32:12.402 --> 32:13.567
You're not gonna be
found guilty.

32:13.603 --> 32:14.702
Seven years.

32:14.737 --> 32:15.870
You're not gonna be
found guilty.

32:15.872 --> 32:18.038
I saw you up there.
You were amazing.

32:18.091 --> 32:21.041
You were that same empathetic,
brilliant man

32:21.043 --> 32:22.143
that I fell in love with.

32:22.178 --> 32:23.394
There's no way
the jury didn't see that.

32:23.446 --> 32:24.812
Rachel, the jury is not
in love with me.

32:24.814 --> 32:26.781
What if all they saw
when they looked at me

32:26.833 --> 32:28.382
was the same fraud
that I've been

32:28.418 --> 32:29.917
since the first day
I took that job?

32:29.919 --> 32:31.602
Is that why you're thinking
about going to prison?

32:31.771 --> 32:33.104
Because what?
You want to punish yourself

32:33.156 --> 32:35.072
and that's your only way
to stop feeling guilty?

32:35.124 --> 32:36.240
Yes, maybe that's
a part of it.

32:36.242 --> 32:37.425
Okay, well it sounds like
it's all of it.

32:37.460 --> 32:38.709
All I know,
is it's the only sure way

32:38.761 --> 32:40.144
to put this to bed
and make sure that

32:40.179 --> 32:42.480
the only person
who is hurt by it is me.

32:42.515 --> 32:44.749
What about me?

32:44.784 --> 32:47.702
Because all I did was love you!

32:47.754 --> 32:49.704
<i>♪
♪</i>

32:50.063 --> 32:52.663
And if you take some deal
that sends you to prison--

32:52.699 --> 32:54.115
Rachel, we can survive this--

32:54.167 --> 32:56.767
Goddamn it, Mike,
they were in on it too!

32:56.803 --> 32:58.469
<i>♪
♪</i>

32:59.106 --> 33:02.190
I'm not gonna rat them out.

33:02.243 --> 33:05.944
And I'm not asking you to.

33:05.996 --> 33:09.031
I'm just asking you
to have faith in yourself.

33:10.801 --> 33:12.901
Okay, I will.

33:12.937 --> 33:18.273
<i>♪
♪</i>

33:19.443 --> 33:21.009
Where the hell were you?

33:21.045 --> 33:22.995
You mean why I wasn't
at the cafe?

33:23.047 --> 33:24.546
I was just coming
to the conclusion

33:24.582 --> 33:26.632
that you could take that threat
and shove it up your ass.

33:26.684 --> 33:28.050
You think I'm bluffing you?

33:28.052 --> 33:30.102
I don't give a shit whether
you're bluffing or not.

33:30.137 --> 33:32.287
It made me sick to let Mike Ross
back into a court.

33:32.323 --> 33:33.822
I'm not letting that
happen again.

33:33.874 --> 33:35.407
I don't think you understand
what's gonna happen to you

33:35.459 --> 33:37.542
when I call Anita Gibbs
tomorrow morning.

33:37.578 --> 33:38.911
You never made a mistake?

33:38.963 --> 33:40.429
You never did something
you regret?

33:40.464 --> 33:42.464
What do you think I'm trying
to fix right now?

33:42.516 --> 33:44.099
Look, if you don't help me,

33:44.151 --> 33:46.234
making sure you never
practice law again

33:46.270 --> 33:47.986
isn't gonna be
on my list of regrets.

33:48.022 --> 33:49.371
You know, I've heard
a lot of people talk

33:49.406 --> 33:52.658
about the great Harvey Specter,
completely unbeatable.

33:52.710 --> 33:53.976
From what I'm seeing,

33:54.011 --> 33:55.677
you're just a bully
who uses other people's fears

33:55.729 --> 33:57.095
to get what he wants.

33:57.147 --> 33:58.263
Well, it's not
gonna happen tonight,

33:58.315 --> 34:00.315
because Mike Ross is
about to go to prison

34:00.351 --> 34:02.784
and I'm not going to stop him.

34:02.820 --> 34:06.254
<i>♪
♪</i>

34:06.290 --> 34:07.623
<i>[knock on door]</i>

34:07.675 --> 34:09.641
[door opens]

34:09.677 --> 34:11.927
<i>♪
♪</i>

34:11.962 --> 34:13.145
Harvey,
it's the middle of the night.

34:13.197 --> 34:14.947
What are you doing here?
I had to see you.

34:14.982 --> 34:16.632
I know you said
I couldn't do this anymore,

34:16.667 --> 34:18.033
but I need to talk to you.

34:18.068 --> 34:20.735
- Talk about what?
- About what I have to do.

34:20.771 --> 34:23.538
You're gonna turn yourself in,
aren't you?

34:23.574 --> 34:27.391
<i>♪
♪</i>

34:27.444 --> 34:29.811
Louis,
the jury didn't come back,

34:29.813 --> 34:30.978
and since they went home,

34:31.031 --> 34:33.447
I'm going home.

34:33.449 --> 34:36.001
So, whatever it is, it's gonna
have to wait until tomorrow.

34:36.036 --> 34:39.170
Tomorrow could be too late.

34:39.223 --> 34:40.839
Too late for what?

34:42.943 --> 34:45.726
This is all his fault.

34:45.728 --> 34:47.129
You didn't start it.

34:47.164 --> 34:48.714
I didn't start it.

34:48.748 --> 34:49.880
He started it.

34:50.201 --> 34:51.440
I'm not having
this conversation

34:51.469 --> 34:52.918
behind Harvey's back.
That's okay.

34:52.969 --> 34:54.803
I already had it to his face.

34:54.839 --> 34:56.319
Tried to get him
to do the right thing

34:56.357 --> 34:58.107
and turn himself in,
but he wouldn't.

34:58.142 --> 34:59.558
I'm not going
to convince him to do that.

34:59.610 --> 35:02.027
I know, because he'll never
be convinced.

35:02.079 --> 35:04.163
Which is why we need
to go to Gibbs together--

35:04.165 --> 35:05.831
- Louis--
- Goddamn it, Jessica,

35:05.833 --> 35:09.301
we don't have any time!

35:09.303 --> 35:13.055
Did it ever occur to you

35:13.107 --> 35:14.807
that if Mike gets found guilty,

35:14.809 --> 35:17.543
the first thing
Harvey is going to do

35:17.578 --> 35:20.446
is walk in there and take
the bullet for me and you?

35:20.448 --> 35:22.081
- No, it didn't.
- Well, it occurred to me.

35:22.116 --> 35:23.882
We turn on him now,

35:23.884 --> 35:26.685
we're not better
than Daniel Hardman

35:26.721 --> 35:28.387
or Charles Forstman

35:28.389 --> 35:32.091
or any of those other people
you despise.

35:32.126 --> 35:35.661
Don't you see?

35:35.696 --> 35:36.962
We could protect each other.

35:37.014 --> 35:39.264
You don't want us to protect
each other, Louis.

35:39.300 --> 35:41.850
You want someone to tell you

35:41.902 --> 35:45.854
that what you're thinking
is okay,

35:45.906 --> 35:49.074
and I'm not going to do that.

35:49.076 --> 35:50.626
Jessica, please.

35:50.661 --> 35:52.578
Good night, Louis.

35:52.630 --> 35:59.051
<i>♪
♪</i>

35:59.726 --> 36:01.459
<i>So you want to</i>
<i>turn yourself in</i>

36:01.495 --> 36:03.161
because some cheater
called you a bully?

36:03.163 --> 36:05.130
No, Donna,
I want to turn myself in

36:05.165 --> 36:07.332
because he was right.
I'm not unbeatable.

36:07.384 --> 36:09.668
No, Harvey, I think
he made you feel guilty,

36:09.670 --> 36:10.969
and now you're not
seeing clearly.

36:11.004 --> 36:12.187
Donna--

36:12.222 --> 36:14.356
Harvey, if it were anybody
other than Mike on trial

36:14.391 --> 36:15.690
and you saw his closing,

36:15.726 --> 36:17.642
do you think that
the jury would convict him?

36:17.694 --> 36:19.611
I don't know, Donna,
but I can't afford

36:19.613 --> 36:20.912
to be wrong about this.

36:20.947 --> 36:22.447
Then let me as you a question:

36:22.449 --> 36:24.582
Why aren't you talking
to Dr. Agard about this?

36:24.618 --> 36:26.338
- How do you know about her?
- Because I do.

36:26.370 --> 36:27.919
And I also know that
the last time you had

36:27.954 --> 36:30.422
a huge decision to make,
you went to her and not me.

36:30.474 --> 36:31.674
Because that was
about business

36:31.725 --> 36:33.141
and this is personal.
No, Harvey,

36:33.176 --> 36:35.143
you didn't go to her
because you know she won't try

36:35.178 --> 36:36.895
to talk you out of this,
but I will.

36:36.947 --> 36:39.564
- Donna--
- Don't do it.

36:39.616 --> 36:40.982
Don't fall
on your sword again.

36:41.034 --> 36:42.734
- I have to--
- No, you don't.

36:42.736 --> 36:43.868
We might not win.

36:43.904 --> 36:45.036
You don't always have
to be the hero.

36:45.038 --> 36:46.788
I'm not doing it
to be the hero.

36:46.840 --> 36:48.206
Then why the hell
are you doing it?

36:48.208 --> 36:51.710
Because
it's my goddamn fault.

36:51.712 --> 36:54.512
<i>[soft music]</i>

36:54.548 --> 36:57.716
No, Harvey, it's not.

36:57.768 --> 37:00.685
It's Mike's fault
just as much as it is yours.

37:00.721 --> 37:02.721
Then why should I be the one
to throw him under the bus?

37:02.773 --> 37:04.556
Don't you get it?
I am not asking you

37:04.558 --> 37:05.857
to throw him under the bus.

37:05.892 --> 37:07.192
I am asking you

37:07.227 --> 37:08.810
to believe that the two of you

37:08.862 --> 37:11.362
are worthy
of being found innocent.

37:11.398 --> 37:12.947
And what if I can't do that?

37:12.983 --> 37:14.733
Then you can march yourself
down to Gibbs's office

37:14.735 --> 37:17.068
in the morning
and turn yourself in.

37:17.070 --> 37:18.953
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:18.989 --> 37:21.790
But I don't want you to do that.

37:21.825 --> 37:23.958
Why not?

37:23.994 --> 37:27.829
Because I think
you're worthy.

37:27.881 --> 37:29.631
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:29.666 --> 37:32.083
And I don't want to lose you.

37:32.085 --> 37:40.091
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:41.978 --> 37:44.095
Harvey,

37:44.147 --> 37:45.680
go to the courthouse
in the morning,

37:45.732 --> 37:47.649
sit with Mike
until that verdict comes in,

37:47.684 --> 37:50.235
and show him
that you have faith in him.

37:50.270 --> 37:52.687
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:52.739 --> 37:55.073
Like I have faith in you.

38:01.211 --> 38:04.047
<i>[soft music]</i>

38:04.049 --> 38:06.883
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:06.935 --> 38:09.919
[cell phone buzzing]

38:13.608 --> 38:15.491
[cell phone beeps]

38:15.527 --> 38:18.077
Hello?

38:18.129 --> 38:20.296
Yeah, this is him.

38:22.300 --> 38:25.234
Yeah, yeah, I'll be right there.

38:25.270 --> 38:27.720
How's the jury back so early?

38:27.772 --> 38:30.523
Oh, it's not the jury.

38:30.558 --> 38:32.525
It's the prosecutor
from the Diaz case.

38:32.560 --> 38:35.478
He wants to talk.

38:35.530 --> 38:37.780
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:37.832 --> 38:39.782
[sighs]

38:39.834 --> 38:44.120
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:44.122 --> 38:45.638
<i>I may have hired a fraud,</i>

38:45.674 --> 38:47.840
<i>but you're the one who had</i>
<i>the chance to turn him in,</i>

38:47.892 --> 38:50.476
<i>and you used his secret to get</i>
<i>what you always wanted...</i>

38:50.512 --> 38:51.894
- Mr. Litt...
<i>- So don't come in here--</i>

38:51.930 --> 38:53.096
I'm sorry to interrupt,

38:53.148 --> 38:55.231
but your cousin Gertrude's
on the phone.

38:55.266 --> 38:56.432
She said she needs to know

38:56.484 --> 38:59.102
whether you found
that old mixed tape of hers.

39:01.156 --> 39:03.906
Tell her I didn't.

39:03.942 --> 39:07.243
Tell her it
must have gotten thrown out,

39:07.278 --> 39:10.863
and to never ask me
about it again.

39:10.915 --> 39:13.249
- Good.
- What do you mean "good"?

39:13.284 --> 39:15.418
I been wanting to tell
Anita Gibbs to go to hell

39:15.453 --> 39:18.588
since this whole thing started.

39:18.623 --> 39:26.045
<i>♪
♪</i>

39:26.097 --> 39:28.264
Mr. Ross,

39:28.299 --> 39:30.600
I'd like to make your client
an offer.

39:30.635 --> 39:32.602
We're listening.

39:32.637 --> 39:34.303
We don't want you, Mr. Diaz.

39:34.356 --> 39:37.890
You said you were just driving
the truck and I believe you,

39:37.942 --> 39:39.308
and we already have
the two gentleman

39:39.310 --> 39:40.610
who committed the actual felony.

39:40.645 --> 39:44.030
So, all you have to do
is testify against them,

39:44.065 --> 39:45.281
and you walk.
What?

39:45.316 --> 39:46.699
Holy shit.
No jail time?

39:46.735 --> 39:48.284
- No jail time.
- Okay that's enough.

39:48.319 --> 39:49.786
I need a moment with my client.
No, I don't need a moment.

39:49.821 --> 39:51.621
I'll take it.
Mr. Diaz, listen to me.

39:51.656 --> 39:53.656
Testifying against your friends
may not seem like a big deal

39:53.708 --> 39:55.375
right now, but it's something
you are gonna have to live with

39:55.410 --> 39:57.577
for the rest of your life.
I don't owe them anything,

39:57.629 --> 39:59.579
and if I can get myself off,
that's what I'm gonna do.

39:59.631 --> 40:00.797
He's only offering you this

40:00.832 --> 40:02.248
because he doesn't have
a case against you.

40:02.300 --> 40:05.835
He's a two-time loser.
I'll make a case against him.

40:05.887 --> 40:08.504
Mr. Diaz...

40:08.556 --> 40:11.507
Give me the pen.

40:11.559 --> 40:14.510
[exhales sharply]
You are making a huge mistake.

40:14.512 --> 40:17.263
Yeah, well, I don't think so,

40:17.315 --> 40:19.232
and if you were in my shoes,
you'd do the exact same thing.

40:19.267 --> 40:21.851
I would never
send my friends to prison.

40:21.903 --> 40:23.186
Yeah, well,
they find me guilty,

40:23.238 --> 40:26.189
they're gonna send my friends
to prison anyways.

40:26.191 --> 40:29.192
<i>[dark alternative music]</i>

40:29.194 --> 40:37.200
<i>♪
♪</i>

40:51.382 --> 40:59.388
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:01.943 --> 41:09.949
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:24.215 --> 41:32.221
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:49.607 --> 41:50.907
Harvey, thank God.

41:50.942 --> 41:53.192
The jury came back.
We have an hour.

41:53.244 --> 41:56.746
- Where's Mike?
- I don't know.

41:56.781 --> 41:58.331
What's the matter?

41:58.366 --> 41:59.699
Harvey?

41:59.751 --> 42:01.033
I have to go.

42:01.085 --> 42:09.091
<i>♪
♪</i>

42:20.572 --> 42:28.561
<i>♪
♪</i>

42:36.321 --> 42:39.872
- You know they're back, right?
- I don't care.

42:39.908 --> 42:42.158
I'm ready to take your deal.

42:42.210 --> 42:43.543
Which one?

